  "description": "Better Crafts: Nautilus Armor is a data pack that allows you to craft nautilus armor [1.21.11 - 26.1.x]",
  "body": "<div align=\"center\">\n  <h1>Better Crafts: Nautilus Armor</h1>\n  <br/>\n  <p>\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Minecraft-1.21.11%2026.1.x-blue?logo=data:image/png;base64,&logoWidth=50\" alt=\"Minecraft\" alt=\"Minecraft\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/License-CC_BY_4.0-blueviolet\" alt=\"License CC BY 4.0\">\n    <a href=\"https://discord.gg/Tq83Zuhduv\" target=\"_blank\">\n      <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/discord/1358706268012810350?color=5865F2&label=Discord&logo=discord&logoColor=white\" alt=\"Discord\">\n    </a>\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/modrinth/dt/cIQjcGCo?logo=modrinth&label=Modrinth\" alt=\"Modrinth\">\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<br/>\n<br/>\n\n<h2>✨ Features</h2>\n<blockquote>\n  This data pack/mod allows you to craft 1 nautilus armor (using all ores) with 5 Ingots of ores and 1 nautilus shell.<br/>\n  In the original version of the game, it is impossible to craft nautilus armor, which is why this mod exists.\n</blockquote>\n\n<br/>\n\n<h2>🧪 Recipes</h2>\n<blockquote>\n  <img src=\"https://nat688.github.io/AllPlugs-datapacks/images/better-crafts/nautilus-armor-copper.png\" alt=\"Copper Nautilus Armor Craft\">\n  <img src=\"https://nat688.github.io/AllPlugs-datapacks/images/better-crafts/nautilus-armor-iron.png\" alt=\"Iron Nautilus Armor Craft\">\n  <img src=\"https://nat688.github.io/AllPlugs-datapacks/images/better-crafts/nautilus-armor-gold.png\" alt=\"Gold Nautilus Armor Craft\">\n  <img src=\"https://nat688.github.io/AllPlugs-datapacks/images/better-crafts/nautilus-armor-diamond.png\" alt=\"Diamond Nautilus Armor Craft\">\n  <img src=\"https://nat688.github.io/AllPlugs-datapacks/images/better-crafts/nautilus-armor-netherite.png\" alt=\"Netherite Nautilus Armor Craft\">\n</blockquote>\n\n<br/>\n\n<h2>📥 Installation</h2>\n<h3>📁 Datapack</h3>\n<blockquote>\n  Drop the <code>.zip</code> file into your world's <code>datapacks</code> folder.<br/>\n  Reload the world or use <code>/reload</code>.<br/>\n  Enjoy your enchanted adventure!\n</blockquote>\n\n<h3>⚙️ Mod</h3>\n<blockquote>\n  Drop the <code>.jar</code> file into the <code>mods</code> folder of your instance.<br/>\n  <code>Restart</code> your game.<br/>\n  Have fun!\n</blockquote>",
